    • Method Detail

      • uploadMedia

        @POST
 @Path(value="/{catalogUuid}/media/upload")
 @Produces(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
 @Consumes(value="multipart/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+form-data")
String uploadMedia(@PathParam(value="catalogUuid")
                                                                                                                                                                                                  String catalogUuid,
                                                                                                                                                                                                  CatalogUploadMediaSpec spec)
        Upload an ISO file as a new media in the given catalog.

        This requires a multi part request payload with the following fields:

        • vdc: the owning VDC of the new media being uploaded
        • file: the file attachment
        • name: the name of the new vApp template
        • description: the description of the new vApp template
        • storage_profile: the storage profile uuid to store the vApp template on, if this field is ommited the VDC default storage profile will be used

        Parameters:
        catalogUuid - catalog uuid
        spec - specification for new media
        Returns:
        asynchronous task details

      • testChunkUploadStatus

        @GET
 @Path(value="/{catalogUuid}/media/upload")
String testChunkUploadStatus(@PathParam(value="catalogUuid")
                                                                              String catalogUuid,
                                                                              @QueryParam(value="resumableIdentifier")
                                                                              String resumableIdentifier,
                                                                              @QueryParam(value="resumableChunkNumber")
                                                                              String resumableChunkNumber,
                                                                              @QueryParam(value="resumableTotalChunks")
                                                                              String resumableTotalChunks)
        Indicates whether a chunk of a file has been received successfully. Will return a 200 response code if the chunk has been received and a 204 if it has not.
        Parameters:
        catalogUuid - catalog uuid
        resumableIdentifier - the file identifier
        resumableChunkNumber - the chunk number to check
        resumableTotalChunks - the total number of chunks for the file
        Returns:
        empty response
